config/shell_history.txt
# Local runtime/user config state written by the settings UI's Save
# actions (#786). Versioned defaults/templates (config/*_default.yaml,
# config/pathing.yaml, config/world_gen_default.yaml) are NOT covered by
# these and stay tracked. config/video.yaml / config/keybinds.yaml /
# config/notifications.yaml — the pre-#786 runtime paths — are ALSO
# tracked (deliberately): their content is a neutral stand-in equal to
# the versioned default/registry, kept only so Engine.Core.Init.
# migrateLegacyConfig always has a readable legacy file to seed a
# direct updater's local file from at first boot. A player who actually
# saved through the old settings UI has a LOCALLY MODIFIED copy of one
# of these paths; git itself refuses to silently overwrite that during
# an update, so their real values survive on disk (now off this list's
# purpose, since the tree no longer needs to protect them) until
# migrateLegacyConfig picks them up. Nothing writes to them any more.
config/video.local.yaml
config/keybinds.local.yaml
config/notifications.local.yaml
saves/
.claude/
.codex/
src/World/Hydrology/DESIGN.md
soil
stone

# Playtest harness session traces (#647) — per-run output, never committed
tools/playtest/sessions/
